We are sad to announce that Kansas Wildlife, Park, & Tourism - Webster State Park has been identified has having the Blue-Green Algae.

Please read the information on this sign.

Additional information can be found at http://www.kdheks.gov/algae-illness/index.htm.

The Beach is CLOSED to all activities.

Boat ramps are still usable and you can still fish.

post_text:
On January 28, 2015 Zach Kesler, Webster State Park Manager and Jana Slansky, Webster State Park Administrative Specialist, were presented the Kansas Wildscape Foundation’s OK Kids Program 2014 Top Site Award. The award was presented to them at the Kansas Park and Recreation Association annual conference held January 27-30 at Topeka Capital Plaza Convention Center.

The staff was selected to receive this award based on their OK Kids Day activities held on May 3, 2014 at Webster State Park. Funding for the activities were made available to them from the Kansas Wildscape Foundation, the Leo Bird Memorial and KDWPT. Activities included: trap shoot, fishing clinic, cast iron cooking demonstration, water bottle rocket demonstration and KDWPT K-9 officer demonstration.

Plans are being made for the 2015 OK Kids Day activities to be held on May 2, 2015.
